[[Image:Marbled polecat.jpg|thumb|right|A [[marbled polecat|marbled '''polecat''']] (weasel-like animal).]]

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|frm|pole|t=hen}} + {{m|en|cat}}. Origin unknown, possible explanations include its fondness for poultry, or the Old English word fol, "foul", because of its smell. The same species was also known as folmart, "foul martin".

